00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:48.000
ANYTHING FROM COMEDIES
TO ACTION MOVIES

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:49.000
AND HORROR FLICKS.

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:51.000
YOU NAME IT, I BET
YOU'VE SEEN IT.

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:53.000
YOU'RE PROBABLY EVEN
THINKING YOU'VE SEEN

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:55.000
SOMETHING LIKE
THIS BEFORE.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:58.000
YOU SEE, FILM IS
A VISUAL LANGUAGE.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.000
JUST LIKE WE HAVE TO LEARN
HOW TO READ AND WRITE,

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.000
YOU HAVE TO LEARN HOW
TO MAKE SENSE OF

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:03.000
WHAT YOU SEE
ON THE SCREEN.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:05.000
WE HAVE TO UNDERSTAND
THE COMPLEX LANGUAGE

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:08.000
OF FILM AND TELEVISION.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:20.000
MOST OF THE FILM AND
TELEVISION PROGRAMS

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:22.000
YOU WATCH BEGIN IN
A PLACE LIKE THIS -

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:23.000
A PRODUCTION HOUSE.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:25.000
THEY BEGIN WITH AN IDEA
WHICH IS USUALLY DISCUSSED

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:29.000
IN A SCRIPT MEETING
LIKE THIS ONE.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:30.000
AND ONCE THE STORY
IS DECIDED UPON

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:32.000
THE WRITER WILL SIT DOWN
AND WRITE THE SCRIPT.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:34.000
HOW'S IT GOING, GANG?

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:36.000
HI JUDY!

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:40.000
THEN THE FINISHED SCRIPT
GOES INTO PRODUCTION.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:41.000
THAT'S WHEN THE CAST
AND CREW TAKE THE SCRIPT

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:44.000
AND SHOOT THE
FILM OR VIDEO.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:50.000
RECORDING AND... ACTION!

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:52.000
AND FINALLY THERE'S
POST-PRODUCTION WHERE

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:54.000
THE FOOTAGE IS EDITED
INTO THE FINAL VERSION

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:56.000
WE SEE ON OUR SCREENS.

00:01:56.000 --> 00:01:58.000
HI GEORGE.

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:00.000
