00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:17.000
FRANK!

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:20.000
SORRY, JUDY, BETTER GO.

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:31.000
WE ALL HAVE OUR
FAVORITE TYPES OF FILMS.

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:35.000
HORROR, ROMANCE, ACTION
AND DRAMA ARE SOME OF

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:37.000
THE MOST POPULAR GENRES.

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:40.000
FOR MOST OF US, WATCHING
ONE OR TWO OF THESE TYPES

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:42.000
OF FILMS WILL GIVE US
ENOUGH OF AN UNDERSTANDING

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:44.000
OF HOW THE NEXT
MOVIE WILL BE.

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:46.000
THIS IS USUALLY BECAUSE
GENRES HAVE CONVENTIONS

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:48.000
THAT ARE EASILY
RECOGNIZABLE.

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:51.000
FOR INSTANCE, HORROR FANS
CAN EXPECT THE KILLER

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:54.000
TO COME BACK AT THE
END FOR ONE LAST SCARE.

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:56.000
PEOPLE WHO LIKE ROMANTIC
COMEDIES KNOW THAT

00:03:56.000 --> 00:03:59.000
THE UNLIKELY COUPLE WILL
EVENTUALLY SHARE A KISS.

00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:02.000
AND A HIGH-OCTANE ACTION
FLICK IS LIKELY TO CONTAIN

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:05.000
AT LEAST ONE CAR CHASE
AND A COUPLE OF EXPLOSIONS

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:07.000
BEFORE THE HERO WINS OUT.

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:10.000
THESE ARE ALL CONVENTIONAL
ELEMENTS OF A GENRE FILM'S

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:12.000
NARRATIVE STRUCTURE.

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:14.000
WE MAKE SENSE OF THE
FILM BY RECOGNIZING

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:17.000
THESE ELEMENTS AND
REACTING TO THEM.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:27.000
RARELY DO NARRATIVE
FILMS DRAW ATTENTION

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:29.000
TO THE STYLISTIC ELEMENTS
THAT HELP MAKE UP

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:32.000
THE FILM'S FORM LIKE
THE LIGHTING, THE SOUND,

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:35.000
THE EDITING, THE
CAMERA ANGLES.

00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:37.000
USUALLY THESE THINGS ARE
HIDDEN FROM THE VIEWER

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:40.000
SO AS TO CREATE A KIND
OF ONSCREEN REALITY.

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:43.000
BUT NOTHING ABOUT FILM IS
REAL, SO WE NEED TO LEARN

00:04:43.000 --> 00:04:45.000
HOW TO RECOGNIZE AND
UNDERSTAND THE DIFFERENT

00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:47.000
FILM TECHNIQUES THAT
HELP A NON-PRINT TEXT

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:49.000
CONVEY MEANING.

00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:54.000
AND RECORDING... AND ACTION!

