00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:16.000
MUCH LIKE A NOVEL OR
SHORT STORY, THE NARRATIVE

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:18.000
ELEMENTS OF A CONVENTIONAL
NARRATIVE FILM

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:20.000
USUALLY UNFOLD
THROUGH ITS CHARACTERS

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:23.000
AND IN PARTICULAR THROUGH
THE CENTRAL CHARACTER,

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:25.000
OR THE PROTAGONIST.

00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:27.000
WE'RE USUALLY INTRODUCED
TO THE PROTAGONIST

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:29.000
AT THE VERY BEGINNING
OF THE FILM.

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:31.000
THE ACTIONS OF THIS
CHARACTER, THE OBSTACLES

00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:33.000
THAT BEFALL HIM OR HER,
AND THE WAY IN WHICH HE

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:36.000
OR SHE DEALS WITH THEM,
USUALLY WORK TO PROPEL

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:39.000
THE STORY FORWARD TO ITS
END POINT, OR CLIMAX.

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:43.000
BUT WHEN WE SEE A FILM
WE DON'T ONLY ENGAGE

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:44.000
WITH THE NARRATIVE,

00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:47.000
NOR DO WE MAKE SENSE
OF A FILM LIKE WE'D

00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:49.000
MAKE SENSE OF A
NOVEL OR SHORT STORY

00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:53.000
- BY INTERPRETING THE
WORDS ON THE PAGE.

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:54.000
A FILM TEXT HAS ITS
OWN UNIQUE WAY OF

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:56.000
COMMUNICATING
WITH THE VIEWER.

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:59.000
IN ORDER FOR US TO FULLY
UNDERSTAND A FILM,

00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:01.000
WE NEED TO UNDERSTAND THE
TECHNIQUES AND FEATURES

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:04.000
OF THE FILM MEDIUM.

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:09.000
THE FOUR POINTS I THINK
ARE A REALLY GOOD GUIDE TO

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:12.000
GETTING ON TOP OF READING
THESE FILMS AS TEXT...

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:14.000
AND THE FOUR POINTS THAT
ARE IMPORTANT FOR US TO

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:16.000
THINK ABOUT WHEN
WE'RE DOING THIS ARE

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:19.000
- CERTAINLY CINEMATOGRAPHY -
WHAT THE CAMERA IS DOING,

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:21.000
THE WAY THE CAMERA
SEES THE ACTION,

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.000
WHERE THE CAMERA
IS PLACED.

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:26.000
SECONDLY, I THINK IT'S
IMPORTANT TO THINK ABOUT

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:29.000
WHAT GOES INTO THE FIELD
OF VISION FOR THE CAMERA

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:32.000
AND THAT'S OFTEN GIVEN
THE TERM "MISE-EN-SCENE",

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:35.000
THE FRENCH TERM WHICH MEANS
LITERALLY THAT WHICH IS

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:38.000
PLACED INTO THE SCENE OR
INTO THE ACTION OF THE SCENE

00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:42.000
AND THAT CAN BE A
VARIOUS RANGE OF THINGS.

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:44.000
THIRDLY, I THINK,
AND IMPORTANTLY

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:45.000
IS THE ISSUE OF SOUND.

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:47.000
WHERE DOES
SOUND COME FROM?

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:48.000
IS IT A SOUNDTRACK?

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:50.000
IS IT A POPULAR SONG?

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:53.000
IS IT PLAYING WITHIN THE
ENVIRONMENT OF THE ACTION

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:57.000
OR IS IT IMPOSED ON
TOP OF THE ACTION?

00:07:58.000 --> 00:08:01.000
FOURTHLY, AND I THINK IN
A SENSE, WHERE THE FILM

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:03.000
IS ACTUALLY MADE IS
IN THE EDITING ROOM.

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:05.000
THE IDEA OF HOW
A FILM IS CUT

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:07.000
OR HOW SHOTS ARE
PUT TOGETHER.

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:33.000
MOST PEOPLE HAVE HEARD OF
EDITING, CAMERA SHOTS

00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:36.000
AND PLACING SOUND TO FILM,
BUT HOW MANY OF THEM

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:38.000
ACTUALLY NOTICE IT?

00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:40.000
AND HOW MANY OF YOU
HAVE HEARD OF THE TERM

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:43.000
MISE-EN-SCENE?

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:47.000
COSTUME AND SCENERY WE
WOULD USUALLY CONSIDER

00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:48.000
AS PART OF
MISE-EN-SCENE:

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:50.000
THAT WHICH IS PUT
INTO THE SCENE.

00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:53.000
WE OFTEN TAKE COSTUME
AND SCENERY FOR GRANTED,

00:08:53.000 --> 00:08:55.000
PARTICULARLY IN
FILMS THAT ARE

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:57.000
SET IN A
CONTEMPORARY SETTING.

00:08:57.000 --> 00:09:00.000
HOWEVER, NOTHING GOES
INTO THE SHOT THAT ISN'T

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:04.000
TOTALLY THE OBJECT OF
SOMEONE'S DESIRE -

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:07.000
USUALLY THE DIRECTOR
OR, IN THIS CASE,

00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:10.000
THE COSTUME DESIGNER
OR THE SET DESIGNER.

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:13.000
WATCH THIS SCENE AGAIN
AND SEE HOW ALTERATIONS

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:15.000
TO THE MISE-EN-SCENE
ALTER THE WAY IN WHICH

00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:18.000
WE PERCEIVE THE ACTION.

