00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:28.000
THESE CHOICES OF COSTUME
AND SET DESIGN HAVE,

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:30.000
AGAIN, A VERY STRONG
IMPRESSION BOTH ON

00:10:31.000 --> 00:10:32.000
THE CHARACTERS
IN THE ACTION

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:36.000
AND ON THE SPECTATOR
VIEWING THE SCENE.

00:10:36.000 --> 00:10:39.000
BEYOND THAT WE THINK ABOUT
THE WAY A SCENE IS LIT.

00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:42.000
NOW THAT MAY ALSO BE SEEN
AS PART OF MISE-EN-SCENE

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:46.000
BUT IT IS IMPORTANT FOR
CINEMATOGRAPHY AS WELL.

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:49.000
CAMERA MEN OR CAMERA
WOMEN ARE ALWAYS

00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:52.000
VERY MUCH CONCERNED ABOUT
THE WAY A SCENE IS LIT

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:55.000
AND HOW THAT IMPACTS ON
WHAT THE CAMERA SEES.

