00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:27.000
BY ALTERING THE LIGHTING
AND CONTRAST OF THE SCENE,

00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:29.000
YOU IMMEDIATELY NOTICE
A CHANGE IN MOOD

00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:30.000
AND ATMOSPHERE.

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:33.000
A DIRECTOR CAN USE THE
LIGHTING TO GUIDE

00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:35.000
THE VIEWER'S ATTENTION
TO CERTAIN OBJECTS

00:11:35.000 --> 00:11:36.000
AND TO CONCEAL OTHERS.

00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:39.000
IT'S JUST LIKE IN A HORROR
MOVIE WHERE THE KILLER

00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:43.000
EMERGES FROM THE DARKNESS
INTO A SHAFT OF LIGHT.

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:45.000
OKAY! HIT THE LIGHTS.

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:46.000
THANKS GUYS.

00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:47.000
WAS THAT IT?

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:50.000
WAS I SCARY ENOUGH?

00:11:55.000 --> 00:11:58.000
SO AS YOU CAN SEE IT'S NOT
JUST THE CHARACTERS' WORDS

00:11:58.000 --> 00:11:59.000
THAT NEED TO
BE UNDERSTOOD.

00:11:59.000 --> 00:12:01.000
FILM IS A
VISUAL LANGUAGE.

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:04.000
AND JUST AS WE LEARN TO
RECOGNIZE LETTERS AND

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:07.000
WORDS AND THE MEANINGS
THAT THEY SIGNIFY, WE ALSO

00:12:07.000 --> 00:12:09.000
NEED TO LEARN TO READ
MOVIE TEXTS AND RECOGNIZE

00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:11.000
THE DIFFERENT ELEMENTS
THAT MAKE UP A FILM'S FORM

00:12:11.000 --> 00:12:15.000
SO AS TO MAKE MEANING
AND DRAW CONCLUSIONS.

00:12:15.000 --> 00:12:17.000
IN SHORT, WE MAKE SENSE
OF FILM BY RECOGNIZING

00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:20.000
